187
00:09:14,989 --> 00:09:16,230
- What did she say?
- What?

188
00:09:16,950 --> 00:09:19,613
I don't know. Sorry, I got distracted.

189
00:09:19,869 --> 00:09:23,408
She's amazing! All of my fears are hers now!

190
00:09:23,498 --> 00:09:24,614
Of course they are.

191
00:09:27,919 --> 00:09:28,919
Um...

192
00:09:29,045 --> 00:09:33,961
I sincerely apologised to you because
I have matured into a fully-formed adult

193
00:09:34,050 --> 00:09:36,007
with empathy and self-awareness.

194
00:09:36,136 --> 00:09:37,843
But if you don't accept my apology

195
00:09:37,887 --> 00:09:42,131
I will smash your stupid art exhibit
into bits!

196
00:09:42,225 --> 00:09:45,059
More Tahani theatrics,
with zero follow-through.

197
00:09:45,311 --> 00:09:47,678
You don't have it in you
to do anything that bold

198
00:09:47,730 --> 00:09:50,222
because I'm the one
who got the boldness gene.

199
00:09:50,316 --> 00:09:52,933
And the good eyebrow gene.

200
00:09:54,070 --> 00:09:55,070
Oh!

201
00:09:55,405 --> 00:09:57,647
Oh, no! All my fears are mine again!

202
00:09:59,117 --> 00:10:01,734
Hey, Davey, can you believe the design
of this room?

203
00:10:01,995 --> 00:10:04,783
Auditorium? More like "audi-bore me-um."

204
00:10:06,291 --> 00:10:07,291
Savage!

205
00:10:07,876 --> 00:10:10,118
Hello, I'm Diana Tremaine.

206
00:10:10,503 --> 00:10:12,790
I never thought I'd run for a PTA board.

207
00:10:13,047 --> 00:10:15,664
For most of my life, I preferred to crawl.

208
00:10:16,509 --> 00:10:18,375
Pub crawl!

209
00:10:18,511 --> 00:10:20,719
But now, I want to make sure kids

210
00:10:20,805 --> 00:10:23,468
in this decommissioned
military bombing test site

211
00:10:23,558 --> 00:10:28,428
