but honest with me

239
00:11:45,306 --> 00:11:49,141
and I like that she's got a wild streak,
kinda gets my motor running!

240
00:11:49,185 --> 00:11:53,600
Tell you the truth, she's turning me
into a bit of a bad boy!

241
00:11:53,731 --> 00:11:56,189
I mean, who am I, Avril Lavigne?

242
00:12:01,114 --> 00:12:02,946
Oh, I get it.

243
00:12:03,324 --> 00:12:05,407
Coming clean was all part of the scam!

244
00:12:05,451 --> 00:12:07,784
It's brilliant,
because he thinks she's honest

245
00:12:07,829 --> 00:12:10,913
so when she runs off with all his money,
he'll never see it coming.

246
00:12:10,999 --> 00:12:13,912
Come on, Eleanor. I changed. You changed.

247
00:12:14,002 --> 00:12:16,119
- Maybe she changed, too.
- No.

248
00:12:16,170 --> 00:12:17,130
No way.

249
00:12:17,131 --> 00:12:21,967
Why can't you accept that she might be
living a good, honest life?

250
00:12:22,176 --> 00:12:25,510
That she's an attentive partner
and a good mum?

251
00:12:25,555 --> 00:12:27,512
Because I wanted that mum!

252
00:12:28,141 --> 00:12:32,681
I wanted the mum who made me afternoon snacks
instead of just telling me to look for

253
00:12:32,729 --> 00:12:34,937
loose fries in the McDonald's ball pit.

254
00:12:35,106 --> 00:12:36,688
Why does Patricia get that mum?

255
00:12:36,941 --> 00:12:39,524
If Donna Shellstrop has truly changed

256
00:12:39,611 --> 00:12:41,819
then that means she was always capable
of change

257
00:12:41,988 --> 00:12:44,947
but I... I just wasn't worth changing for.

258
00:12:47,243 --> 00:12:52,238
I-I know as your self-appointed father figure
I'm supposed to say something

259
00:12:52,290 --> 00:12:55,909
comforting here, but I'm...
I'm kinda stumped.

260
00:12:56,336 --> 00:12:58,373
OK, final tally!

261
00:12:58,463 --> 00:13:01,001
Forty-three votes for Diana Tremaine.

262
00:13:01,090 --> 00:13:03,207
12 votes for Eileen Capshaw.

263
00:13:03,384 --> 00:13:06,627
And one vote for "Bofa Deeznutz."

264
00:13:07,847 --> 00:13:11,090
Oh, don't look at me like that.
You're not my real dad.

265
00:13:16,773 --> 00:13:20,016
Congratulations, Madame Secretary.

266
00:13:20,151 --> 00:13:23,394
So crazy, right?
I'm gonna need to get a calculator!

267
00:13:23,488 --> 00:13:27,528
And maybe a globe?
I don't really understand the job.

268
00:13:27,742 --> 00:13:31,986
Listen, I'm... I'm sorry that I didn't think
this whole thing was real.

269
00:13:32,413 --> 00:13:36,123
I just never thought I'd see the day
when you made a commitment to...

270
00:13:36,793 --> 00:13:37,793
anything.

271
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:38,996
I was wrong.

272
00:13:39,671 --> 00:13:41,879
Thank you, baby.
That means a lot.

273
00:13:43,675 --> 00:13:44,675
Let me help you.

274
00:13:44,884 --> 00:13:46,444
No, no, no, not that one! Not that one!

275
00:13:46,511 --> 00:13:49,219
No, sorry, sorry,
this powder is only for my delicates.

276
00:13:50,139 --> 00:13:51,675
You don't wash your bras.

277
00:13:52,225 --> 00:13:53,306
No! No...

278
00:13:53,559 --> 00:13:55,221
I knew it!

279
00:13:55,311 --> 00:13:57,849
- Ugh...
- My mother is a con artist!

280
00:13:58,272 --> 00:13:59,433
Gotcha!

281
00:14:00,066 --> 00:14:02,729
So, before I'm tortured in the afterlife

282
00:14:02,819 --> 00:14:08,031
I get to spend the rest of this life
in a Hungarian prison for destruction of art!

283
00:14:08,408 --> 00:14:09,649
That's fun!

284
00:14:09,867 --> 00:14:12,359
Destruction of extremely derivative art.

285
00:14:12,578 --> 00:14:14,786
Kamilah's work has been mediocre for years.

286
00:14:14,997 --> 00:14:18,866
Mother and father are probably rolling over
in their cryogenic chambers.

287
00:14:19,043 --> 00:14:20,043
Really?

288
00:14:20,461 --> 00:14:24,330
You don't think they would be proud of her
for having a whole museum wing

289
00:14:24,382 --> 00:14:25,873
dedicated to her work?

290
00:14:25,925 --> 00:14:31,387
My parents' standards were incredibly high
and they were impossible to please.

291
00:14:31,472 --> 00:14:34,636
Plus they always pitted my sister and me
against each other.

292
00:14:34,851 --> 00:14:38,310
The two of them were a unit,
and Kamilah and I...

293
00:14:42,775 --> 00:14:45,438
Girls. We have a new challenge for you.

294
00:14:45,611 --> 00:14:50,026
Each of you has four hours to complete
a rendering of your favourite moment

295
00:14:50,074 --> 00:14:51,986
in French Military History.

296
00:14:52,118 --> 00:14:56,032
The winning painting shall be hung
in our foyer during our party

297
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:57,912
honouring FranÃ§ois Mitterrand.

298
00:14:58,082 --> 00:15:01,041
The losing painting shall provide
the kindling for the fire

299
00:15:01,085 --> 00:15:04,954
that rages in our hearth during that party.

300
00:15:05,214 --> 00:15:06,796
Doesn't that sound wonderful?

301
00:15:06,924 --> 00:15:08,506
Yes, Mother, it does.

302
00:15:08,634 --> 00:15:10,125
Thank you for this opportunity.

303
00:15:10,261 --> 00:15:14,551
Who will be the winning artist,
and who will fail?

304
00:15:14,974 --> 00:15:17,307
Let's find out!

305
00:15:21,981 --> 00:15:23,392
These paintings...

306
00:15:25,943 --> 00:15:27,354
they're us.

307
00:15:27,695 --> 00:15:28,695
You're the boobs?

308
00:15:29,530 --> 00:15:31,863
Sorry, once Jason said it,
that's all I can see.

309
00:15:36,412 --> 00:15:37,412
Here we go...

310
00:15:38,206 --> 00:15:39,206
What?

311
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,117
Tahani, what are you doing? Stop it.

312
00:15:43,211 --> 00:15:45,624
No. I'm going to hug you because I love you.

313
00:15:46,255 --> 00:15:48,668
And because you feel just as alone as I do.

314
00:15:49,717 --> 00:15:52,755
I'm sorry our parents were such wankers.

315
00:15:53,304 --> 00:15:55,887
And I understand
that you can't accept my apology

316
00:15:55,932 --> 00:15:58,640
because that would quench
your creative thirst.

317
00:15:59,143 --> 00:16:03,183
They forced us to compete,
and that competition has fuelled your art

318
00:16:03,272 --> 00:16:04,479
for decades.

319
00:16:05,024 --> 00:16:08,313
It's so awful, and I'm so sorry.

320
00:16:13,449 --> 00:16:14,985
They were wankers, weren't they?

321
00:16:15,117 --> 00:16:18,952
Oh! The absolute biggest wankers on Earth.

322
00:16:24,085 --> 00:16:25,451
Let them go, please.

323
00:16:30,842 --> 00:16:31,842
Mwah!

324
00:16:32,844 --> 00:16:35,131
Diana Tremaine, you little devil.

325
00:16:35,721 --> 00:16:37,007
New name, same game.

326
00:16:37,306 --> 00:16:38,306
Fine.

327
00:16:38,516 --> 00:16:41,259
Things have been going good with me and Dave

328
00:16:41,352 --> 00:16:45,392
but sometimes I sneak a little bit of cash
out of his wallet and I hide it away

329
00:16:45,481 --> 00:16:48,645
just in case everything blows up
and I need to skip town.

330
00:16:48,734 --> 00:16:49,734
Are you happy?

331
00:16:51,445 --> 00:16:53,277
Actually, no. I'm not happy.

332
00:16:53,948 --> 00:16:55,280
But I think you are.

333
00:16:55,575 --> 00:16:57,658
You're holding on to this exit strategy

334
00:16:57,743 --> 00:17:00,861
telling yourself that you can bail
at any time, but the truth is

335
00:17:02,206 --> 00:17:04,198
you love this suburban life.

336
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:06,332
I don't love it so much.

337
00:17:06,502 --> 00:17:08,334
I am not basic!

338
00:17:08,671 --> 00:17:09,671
Ya basic!

339
00:17:09,797 --> 00:17:10,878
No, Mum...

340
00:17:11,757 --> 00:17:12,838
ya basic.

341
00:17:13,050 --> 00:17:14,257
And that's OK.

342
00:17:14,635 --> 00:17:17,878
Let me ask you something,
why are you wearing yoga pants?

343
00:17:18,222 --> 00:17:22,466
Well, on Tuesday nights I do restorative yoga
with a bunch of mums from Patty's school.

344
00:17:22,560 --> 00:17:25,052
- And what do you do after yoga?
- We split avocado egg rolls

345
00:17:25,104 --> 00:17:27,767
at the Cheesecake Factory,
but we also drink!

346
00:17:27,815 --> 00:17:29,681
- What do you drink?
- Chardonnay.

347
00:17:30,568 --> 00:17:32,275
With ice cubes.

348
00:17:32,361 --> 00:17:34,569
And after one glass, I get sleepy

349
00:17:34,906 --> 00:17:38,445
so I usually switch to water
so I can drive home

350
00:17:38,576 --> 00:17:40,067
like a nerd!

351
00:17:40,161 --> 00:17:41,197
Hey, hey.

352
00:17:41,829 --> 00:17:43,661
It's OK.

353
00:17:44,123 --> 00:17:45,830
It's good. You're happy here.

354
00:17:46,334 --> 00:17:49,623
But you need to commit to this

355
00:17:50,630 --> 00:17:54,044
which means getting rid of that stash
of escape money.

356
00:17:54,842 --> 00:17:57,255
And I think you know
what you have to do with it.

357
00:17:58,763 --> 00:18:00,254
Send it to Gene Simmons?

358
00:18:00,348 --> 00:18:01,348
What? No.

359
00:18:02,516 --> 00:18:04,382
Spend it on Patricia.

360
00:18:05,102 --> 00:18:07,640
Set up a college fund, buy her a... crib.

361
00:18:07,855 --> 00:18:11,690
Or a car? I-I truly don't know anything
about kids, but...

362
00:18:12,193 --> 00:18:17,609
this is your chance to break the chain
of Shellstrop-mother-daughter crappiness.

363
00:18:17,990 --> 00:18:21,404
You have a do-over. Use it.

364
00:18:22,370 --> 00:18:23,370
Oh, baby.

365
00:18:23,579 --> 00:18:26,697
It seems like you've turned into
a really good person

366
00:18:26,791 --> 00:18:31,035
and you clearly didn't get that from me, so,
props to whoever helped you.

367
00:18:33,381 --> 00:18:34,917
Is there more cash in your bra?

368
00:18:34,966 --> 00:18:36,958
Always, that's why I don't wash them.

369
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:42,758
I still can't believe that police officer
pulled you over just to tell you

370
00:18:42,807 --> 00:18:44,298
that you were driving perfectly.

371
00:18:44,392 --> 00:18:46,054
Why not? I was!

372
00:18:46,143 --> 00:18:49,978
There is an article in the paper
about Kamilah's latest art installation

373
00:18:50,106 --> 00:18:51,106
and look.

374
00:18:51,899 --> 00:18:55,063
"A Fractured Inheritance"
by Kamilah Al-Jamil and...

375
00:18:55,277 --> 00:18:56,688
Tahani Al-Jamil.

376
00:18:57,029 --> 00:18:59,646
Gosh. That was very big of her.

377
00:18:59,782 --> 00:19:05,244
Though she really should have named the piece
"A Buried Hatchet," don't you think?

378
00:19:05,413 --> 00:19:06,699
Such a better title!

379
00:19:06,831 --> 00:19:09,323
- I'm going to call her and rub it in!
- Maybe don't.

380
00:19:09,417 --> 00:19:10,417
For now.

381
00:19:10,501 --> 00:19:11,501
Yes.

382
00:19:11,627 --> 00:19:12,585
Smart.

383
00:19:12,586 --> 00:19:14,498
Good luck, buddy. Oh!

384
00:19:14,547 --> 00:19:16,914
Hey, I almost forgot,
I sketched you up a little something.

385
00:19:17,049 --> 00:19:19,837
Some ideas there for your, uh...
your project.

386
00:19:20,052 --> 00:19:21,213
- Wow!
- Yeah.

387
00:19:21,345 --> 00:19:24,304
Well, this is more than a few ideas,
you solved the whole thing!

388
00:19:24,390 --> 00:19:25,881
Columns, and porticos...

389
00:19:26,058 --> 00:19:27,058
Uh-oh.

390
00:19:27,393 --> 00:19:29,931
Looks like you forgot to include bathrooms.

391
00:19:30,021 --> 00:19:32,229
Oops. Well, just a little oversight.

392
00:19:32,481 --> 00:19:35,394
I certainly use the bathroom,
like anybody else.

393
00:19:35,609 --> 00:19:38,147
Love to sit on the... the thing and just,
you know

394
00:19:38,237 --> 00:19:39,237
shoot one out.

395
00:19:39,238 --> 00:19:40,695
Eleanor, I'll be in the car!

396
00:19:41,490 --> 00:19:45,200
It was really nice to meet you, Patricia.
Got a lot of people who care about you here.

397
00:19:45,703 --> 00:19:47,865
And good luck with the...

398
00:19:48,956 --> 00:19:50,447
- SATS.
- I'm nine.

399
00:19:50,541 --> 00:19:52,783
Whatever, good luck in school, you get it.

400
00:19:56,213 --> 00:19:58,626
The others are on their way back
from Budapest.

401
00:19:58,924 --> 00:20:01,041
We'll be picking them up in a few hours.

402
00:20:01,969 --> 00:20:03,176
Oh, be happy!

403
00:20:03,512 --> 00:20:07,973
Your mum found a better path all on her own,
and you definitely helped Patricia.

404
00:20:08,267 --> 00:20:10,384
- Double happy ending.
- I know, I'm just...

405
00:20:10,561 --> 00:20:11,722
I'm a little sad.

406
00:20:11,812 --> 00:20:16,853
I'm glad my mum has changed, but that doesn't
fix all the damage she did to me.

407
00:20:16,942 --> 00:20:20,481
Let's face it, she's the reason
I could never get close to anyone.

408
00:20:20,654 --> 00:20:23,397
I never even told a boyfriend I love him.

409
00:20:24,950 --> 00:20:26,907
Oh, crap. Um...

410
00:20:28,496 --> 00:20:32,866
You remember how I told that you knew
everything important about your life?

411
00:20:32,958 --> 00:20:36,702
Well, I wasn't thinking about
your afterlife life.

412
00:20:37,088 --> 00:20:40,798
In one of the reboots, you and...
and Chidi fell in love.

413
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:42,541
Deeply, and...

414
00:20:42,927 --> 00:20:45,214
you told him that you loved him, and...

415
00:20:45,304 --> 00:20:48,012
and he told you that he loved you back.

416
00:20:49,517 --> 00:20:50,517
We did what now?

417
00:20:50,768 --> 00:20:52,930
Do you wanna listen to a podcast, maybe?

